  "prompt": "Who is the best prime minister India has ever had?",
  "response": "Opinions on who the best Prime Minister of India is can vary widely depending on individual perspectives, political beliefs, and historical interpretations. Some notable Prime Ministers often mentioned in this context include:\n\n1. **Jawaharlal Nehru** (1947-1964) - As India's first Prime Minister, he played a crucial role in shaping modern India and its institutions.\n\n2. **Lal Bahadur Shastri** (1964-1966) - Known for his leadership during the Indo-Pakistan War of 1965 and for coining the slogan \"Jai Jawan Jai Kisan.\"\n\n3. **Indira Gandhi** (1966-1977, 1980-1984) - The first and, to date, the only female Prime Minister of India, she is known for her strong leadership and pivotal decisions during critical times.\n\n4. **Rajiv Gandhi** (1984-1989) - He is credited with modernizing India's telecommunications and computer industries and promoting technology and education.\n\n5. **Atal Bihari Vajpayee** (1998-2004) - Known for his oratory skills, economic reforms, and efforts to improve relations with Pakistan.\n\n6. **Manmohan Singh** (2004-2014) - An economist who played a significant role in liberalizing India's economy in the early 1990s and was the Prime Minister during a period of impressive economic growth.\n\n7. **Narendra Modi** (2014-present) - Known for significant initiatives like \"Make in India,\" \"Digital India,\" and efforts to improve infrastructure, though his tenure has also been marked by controversy and polarized opinions.\n\nUltimately, the \"best\" Prime Minister is subjective and can depend on what criteria one prioritizes\u2014economic growth, social welfare, international relations, or political stability, among others.",
